    This lecture provides an introduction to boundary value problems for
    linear and nonlinear elliptic differential equations of second order. We
    will discuss Sobolev spaces, which rely
    on a generalized notion of differentiability, variational problems
    and the associated operator equations, monotone operators, Galerkin
    methods and linear finite elements as well as the Lax-Milgram lemma and
    the theorem of Zarantonello.
